Other distributions that can be modeled with a PMF include the [categorical distribution](/Categorical_distribution) (a generalization of the Bernoulli) and the [multinomial distribution](/Multinomial_distribution).

*   If a discrete distribution has two or more categories, and a single trial determines which one occurs, this is a **categorical distribution**.
*   The **multinomial distribution** provides an example of a [multivariate discrete distribution](/Joint_probability_distribution). Here, the random variables represent the number of successes in each category after a fixed number of trials. The PMF gives the probability for a specific combination of success counts across all categories.

